						               													<description>Players are young wizards who fight over magic gems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At his/her turn, one plays Hocus cards, while every player can play Pocus cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; The 50 red Hocus cards are powerful 9 different spells allowing players to draw cards, take or steal gems, force an opponent to discard cards, look at the cards on the top of the pile&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; The 25 yellow Pocus cards can only be combined with a Hocus card already in play, modifying its effects in order to protect oneself against a evil spell, double the effect of any spell, remove all other Pocus cards in play&amp;hellip; There're 8 different Pocus cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every wizard has always 3 of his/her cards face up in front of him/her, so every player partially knows the hand of all the others.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of his/her turn, a player can either draw 2 cards or take 1 gem from the magic cauldron. The game ends whenever the cauldron is empty, and the player with the most gems wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
